From 9809c7e813522d71c3e777fcfd2a1da180c503e0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Crispin <john@phrozen.org>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 07:04:38 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 111/149] mediatek: add xHCI USBIF compliance toolkit sources

Patch 0108 (mediatek: import kernel 6.12 patches from MediaTek SDK)
wired up xhci-mtk-{chgdt-en,discth,hstx-srctrl,intr-en,preemphasic,reg,
term-vref,test,unusual,vrt-vref}.o build targets in the xhci-mtk
Makefile under CONFIG_USB_XHCI_MTK_DEBUGFS, but the source files
themselves were not imported, so enabling the option fails to build.

Add the 14 source files from the MediaTek 25.12 feeds at
files/target/linux/mediatek/files-6.12/drivers/usb/host/.

Signed-off-by: John Crispin <john@phrozen.org>
